-- China to Introduce Tax Break for Alternative Energy Usage, Xinhua Reports
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2010-09-28T00:42:28Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-28/china-to-introduce-tax-break-for-alternative-energy-industry-xinhua-says.html
China will introduce tax breaks for
industries including alternative energy utilization, resources
development and agricultural processing, the Xinhua News Agency
reported today, citing vice finance minister Wang Jun.  The country will offer financial subsidies to support
competitive industries in central China, according to the
report.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
